 <section xml:id="joining-the-community"
          xmlns='http://docbook.org/ns/docbook' version='5.0' xml:lang='en'
          xmlns:xsi='http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance'
          xsi:schemaLocation='http://docbook.org/ns/docbook http://docbook.org/xml/5.0/xsd/docbook.xsd'
          xmlns:xlink='http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink'>
 <title>Joining the ForgeRock Community</title>

 <para>After you <link xlink:show="new"
                       xlink:href="https://idp.forgerock.org/openam/UI/Login?service=register"
 >sign up</link> to join the ForgeRock community, you can edit the Community
 <link xlink:href="https://wikis.forgerock.org/" xlink:show="new">Wikis</link>,
 and also log bugs and feature requests in the <link xlink:show="new"
                                                     xlink:href="https://bugster.forgerock.org/">issue tracker</link>.</para>

 <para>If you have a question regarding a project but cannot find an answer in
 the project documentation or Wiki, browse to the <link xlink:show="new"
                                                        xlink:href="http://forgerock.org">Developer Community</link> page for the
 project, where you can find details on joining the project mailing lists, and
 find links to mailing list archives. You can also suggest updates to documentation
 through the <link
  xlink:href="https://lists.forgerock.org/mailman/listinfo/docs"
  xlink:show="new">ForgeRock docs mailing list</link>.</para>

 <para>The Community Wikis describe how to check out and build source code.
 Should you want to contribute a patch, test, or feature, or want to author
 part of the core documentation, first have a look on the ForgeRock site
 at <link xlink:href="http://forgerock.org/get_involved.html" xlink:show="new"
  >how to get involved</link>.</para>
</section>
